{"cursor":"35734","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n modem/router. A modern example of an embedded system. Labelled parts include a\n microprocessor (4), RAM (6), and flash memory (7).]]\n\nAn 'embedded system' is a computer system designed for specific control\nfunctions within a larger system, often with real-time computing\nconstraints. It is embedded as part\nof a complete device often including hardware and mechanical parts. By contrast,\na general-purpose computer, such as a personal computer (PC), is designed to be\nflexible and to meet a wide range of end-user needs. Embedded systems control\nmany devices in common use today.\n\nEmbedded systems contain processing cores that are either microcontrollers or\ndigital signal processors (DSP).\n\nA processor is an important unit in the embedded system hardware. It is the\nheart of the embedded system.\n\nThe key characteristic, however, is being dedicated to handle a particular task.\nSince the embedded system is dedicated to specific tasks, design engineers can\noptimize it to reduce the size and cost of the product and increase the\nreliability and performance. Some embedded systems are mass-produced, benefiting\nfrom economies of scale.\n\nPhysically, embedded systems range from portable devices such as digital watches\nand MP3 players, to large stationary installations like traffic lights, factory\ncontrollers. Complexity varies from low, with a single microcontroller chip, to\nvery high with multiple units, peripherals and networks mounted inside a large\nchassis or enclosure.\n","linknr":574,"url":"Embedded_Devices","recorded":1362688926,"links":64,"instances":["icsp","programming_language","software","computing","programming","missile","computing","computing","computing","networking","standard"],"pdf":["http://www.microvga.com/pdf/uvga-text-ds.pdf","http://www.usenix.org/publications/login/2007-12/pdfs/heiser.pdf","http://www.clarinox.com/docs/whitepapers/Whitepaper_06_CrossPlatformDiscussion.pdf","http://www.clarinox.com/docs/whitepapers/Whitepaper_06_CrossPlatformDiscussion.pdf"],"categories":["Embedded systems|"],"headings":["Variety of embedded systems","History","Characteristics","Embedded software architectures","See also","Notes","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg/40px-Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/ADSL_modem_router_internals_labeled.jpg/300px-ADSL_modem_router_internals_labeled.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/Overo_with_coin.jpg/220px-Overo_with_coin.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6f/ESOM270_eSOM300_Computer_on_Modules.jpg/220px-ESOM270_eSOM300_Computer_on_Modules.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/MicroVGA_TUI_demoapp.jpg/220px-MicroVGA_TUI_demoapp.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Nuvola_apps_ksim.png/28px-Nuvola_apps_ksim.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/df/Wikibooks-logo-en-noslogan.svg/40px-Wikibooks-logo-en-noslogan.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Wikiversity-logo.svg/40px-Wikiversity-logo.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["router","computing"],["router","computing"],["minuteman","missile"],["menu","computing"],["router","comp